Class Order

java.lang.Object
common.Order
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
WaitingList
public class Order extends Object implements Serializable
Represents an order for visiting a park. Each order contains information such as the visitor's ID, the park's number, the number of visitors, the price, the date and time of the visit, the visitor's email, the telephone number, the order status, and the type of order.

      Parameters:
      orderId - The unique identifier of the order.
      visitorId - The ID of the visitor who placed the order.
      parkNumber - The number of the park to be visited.
      amountOfVisitors - The number of visitors in the order.
      price - The price of the order.
      visitorEmail - The email of the visitor who placed the order.
      date - The date of the visit.
      visitTime - The time of the visit.
      statusStr - The status of the order as a string.
      typeOfOrderStr - The type of the order as a string.
      telephoneNumber - The telephone number associated with the order.
      parkName - The name of the park to be visited.
